Multi-modal RAG with LangChain for Intelligent Document Retrieval

Overview
This project implements a multi-modal Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline using LangChain, Pinecone, and Llama-3.1 for intelligent document retrieval. The solution enables automated extraction, summarization, and retrieval of relevant information from PDFs, leveraging OCR to extract text from images.

Features
- Multi-modal document retrieval
- Automated extraction and summarization of relevant information
- OCR-based text extraction from images
- Intelligent search and retrieval capabilities

Technologies Used
- LangChain
- Pinecone
- Llama-3.1
- Groq
- OCR (Optical Character Recognition)

Requirements
- Python 3.x
- LangChain library
- Pinecone library
- Llama-3.1 model
- Groq library
- OCR library (e.g., Tesseract)

Installation
1. Set up LangChain, Pinecone, and Llama-3.1


